Stir together peanut butter, apple butter, and optional caramel sauce in a medium sized bowl. Mix cinnamon into the graham cracker crumbs and add to the apple butter mixture. Combine well. Chill for at least 30 minutes. Scoop Tablespoon-sized balls of the mixture onto a wax paper-lined cookie sheets (dough will be soft). Roll into uniform-sized balls. Place chopped peanuts in a small bowl and roll the balls in them to coat. Store in refrigerator.